adviseScripts.text: Master, guess!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What's got looong ears and a fluffy tail?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: And when you look into its eyes,
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: you just can't help but fall in love with it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Twinkling Rabbit.
A rabbit.
Wait, could you be referring to me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: S-so... you've f-fallen in love with me? Ohmygoshohmygosh!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: That's right!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Rabbits are just always soooo cute, hehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I have a conversation about rabbits.
I love the color green!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: It just gives me this fresh and clean feeling.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What's your favorite color, Master?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Green.
Black.
Wow, that's just like me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Can I ask why you like it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Because it's the same color as your hair.
Oh my gosh, really?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Just kidding.
Hmph... you're just saying that because you're shy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Black? That's... not really my cup of tea.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Black stains are the toughest to get out!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I have a conversation about our favorite colors.
Master! Master!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: If you suddenly had a lot of money, what would you spend it on?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I wouldn't spend it on anything.
I'd go to the Maid Cafe every day.
You mean... you wouldn't come to the Maid Cafe at all?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: How sad... *Sob*
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Wow, really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Just the thought of you coming here every day gets me so excited!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I spend time getting lost in our joyful imaginings.
I just can't get enough of Coin Rush's beds. They're so clean and white!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: As soon as I see those neatly arranged pillows and blankets,
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I just get this feeling like everything's going to be fine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I wonder where I can learn to make a bed so neatly?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I think you're capable of doing it now.
Ask Mustang.
You think so? Hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: All right, then. I'll make your bed today!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: *Sob*
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: It's tough to get some time in with Boss...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Isn't there any other way?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I discuss about other cleaning procedures.
Master! Do you know that when it comes to cleaning,
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: it's important to do things in a proper order?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Tell me, what should you do first when cleaning the floor?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sweep the floor.
Mop the floor.
No, no, you need to mop first!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: That way, you don't kick up as much dust.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: It's okay if you're not overly familiar with this stuff.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Looks like I'll have to clean your room from now on.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Whoa! How did you know that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: That's a tip that Cocoa doesn't even know about.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Do you still need me to clean your room...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I talk about the order of cleaning.
I saw that omurice was served for breakfast,
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: and it makes me miss Cocoa and Ade so much...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What do you think they are doing right now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: They're probably working like they always are.
They're probably missing you loads too.
Oh boy... it must be awfully busy since I'm not there.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I really need to come in first and hurry back there!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Oh, Cocoa... Ade...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: *Wail*
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I miss them so much!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: *Wail*
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I've got to make sure I come in first place so that the Maid Cafe doesn't go under.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I can count on you, can't I, Master?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Of course.
*Sobs* Thanks, Master!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I comfort Soda until she calms down.
Master... I feel like you've been staring at me for a while.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Is there something you wanted to say?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: You've got some dust on your face.
You look adorable in that rabbit outfit.
*Gasp* I do?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: How long has it been there?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Aw, man... I better go wash my face again.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Oh my gosh, really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Now, I want to wear these kinds of outfits all the time!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I spend some time together happily.
Alice said that she'll visit the Maid Cafe sometime.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What should I serve to make her happy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Beef Bourguignon.
Omurice.
Beef bou... bour... er...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: But I've never made that before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I better practice before Alice comes to visit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: That I can handle!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I'll chop the carrots extra fine, so I'm sure Alice will love that, hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I knew it'd be a good idea to ask you for advice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Thank you, Master!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I talk more about Maid Cafe's menu.
There we go, nice and squeaky clean! After a thorough cleaning, I always crave pudding.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What are you in the mood for, Master?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: An adult beverage.
Some dessert.
An... adult beverage?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I don't think I've ever tried that before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Can I have one too?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, we're craving for the same things!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: It just so happens I brought some pudding with me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Would you like to share it with me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I have a pleasant time talking about food.
Master, I had a nice dream yesterday!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Guess what it was about!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Cleaning.
Me.
Hehe, bingo!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Cleaning is always a blast, even in my dreams.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What? No, it was about cleaning.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Although it'd be nice if you showed up too...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I talk about dreams.
Today, someone at Coin Rush
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: told me that
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I look like a rabbit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What do you think they meant?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Maybe they're telling you not to hop around?
Maybe they think you're as cute as a rabbit.
Oh!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I was in a rush to meet Alice on the second floor...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I'll try and be more careful from now on.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: R-really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Me, cute? But I'm not nearly as cute and petite as Alice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sure, you're not as petite as her, but that just means you're extra cute.
It... it does?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I'm not quite sure I follow, but I'm happy anyway! Hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I attempt to decipher what the customer could have meant.
I'm a big fan of hotel blankets. They smell so lovely!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: It seems like they've been sprayed with something nice, and I'd like to give it a try.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: So, what scent do you think would best suit me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sweet baby powder.
Fresh lemon.
Hmm... baby powder?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: It sounds like something nice and cozy that'd induce sleep.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: That'd be perfect for spraying on a bed!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for the great recommendation!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I love lemon as much as the next person,
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: but I'm not sure if it'd go great on bedding.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I mean, that's something I mainly use for cleaning,
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: so if I were to smell that, I might suddenly get the urge to clean. *Sob*
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I have a conversation about which scent to spray on bedding.
Master, I've been invited to a performance celebrating the end of the Golden Chip event.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What should I wear?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: A maid outfit.
A bunny outfit.
Since I’m here representing Maid For You, that sounds like the best idea, doesn't it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for the suggestion, Master!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Huh? Even when the event is over?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: It's a bit tricky for me to wear that, but... okay.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I look into what outfit she should wear for the occasion.
Master, Blanc just taught me how to play a game called "Odd or Even".
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: So, you have to guess whether I have an odd or even number of coins in my hand. Do you want to try it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sure.
All right, then!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Odd or even?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Even.
Odd.
Wow, you guessed correctly right off the bat!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: You're good at this, Master!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sorry, but it was even.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Would you like to try again?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I play Odd or Even with Soda all day long.
Master! If another member of Maid For You were to wear a bunny outfit,
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: who would you want to see?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I can't decide...
Ade.
Hehe, me neither.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I think everyone would look simply adorable!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Eh? Ade?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Hmm… I think she’d say that wearing a maid outfit is integral to being a maid...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: What if you tried one on instead?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I have a fun time letting our imaginations run wild.
Master, I heard that getting rid of bad luck is more important than chasing after good luck!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Do you know any ways to remove bad luck?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Toss some salt over your shoulder.
I'm not too sure... I only believe in myself.
Huh?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: But the floor would get all messy...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Salt is supposed to ward off bad luck.
Oh, I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: In that case, it's okay. I'll just be a bit more diligent with my cleaning!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Oh dear... that sounds a bit tough.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I'll help you.
Aw, thanks!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I'll give it my all until the games are over!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I have a conversation about ways to remove bad luck.
Master, if I get first place in the next game, will you watch a movie with me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sure.
Woohoo! What kind of genre do you like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Film noir.
Rom-coms.
Oh... aren't those movies filled with all sorts of seedy characters?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sounds kinda scary...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Can't we watch something else?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sounds like a nice and upbeat genre. I like it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I'll do my best to win so that we can watch one together!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I talk about movie genres.
*Shake shake*
As I wake up, I can faintly make out a blurry white furball moving in front of me.
Poke it hard.
Gently pet it.
Oh, Master! Are you awake?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Oh, sorry for surprising you. I didn't realize that was your tail.
It's okay.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Since you were asleep, I figured I'd take the opportunity to clean up your room.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sorry if I woke you up...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: *Shake shake*
Is it... a tail?
Oh, Master! Are you awake?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I was wondering why my back felt warm all of a sudden. I thought it was the sunlight, but it was you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Sorry for surprising you. I didn't realize that was your tail.
It's okay, and it's a great morning today!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I spend a pleasant morning together.
Master, what do you think makes bunny outfits so mesmerizing?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Their sexiness.
Their adorability.
Sexy, you say?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: But don't they have a cute tail and bunny ears?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... I'm not too sure...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I feel the same too, hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Whenever I see Alice dressed up in these outfits, I just wanna hug her 'cause she's so cute!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Soda and I talk about how mesmerizing the bunny outfits are.
Master! Would you rather wash dishes for ten people,
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: or clean the bathroom?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Wash dishes.
Neither.
Even if it's for that many people?
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: That's because I hate cleaning the bathroom...
I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: Well, I already did the dishes...
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: but that's okay!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I like cleaning the bathroom too, hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: C'mon, you have to choose one!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I really can't. Sorry.
Okay, fine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I'll just do both, hehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Soda

adviseScripts.text: I watch Soda happily clean.
